  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6576.58 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6570 (-77.5B) and positive gamma at 6600 (+30.8B), dealers are currently in forced buying mode as they're short gamma and need to chase this move higher. The -69% 1-min and -288% 5-min GEX changes signal dealers just got massively short gamma, creating a breakout regime where they'll amplify moves by buying rallies toward 6600 and aggressively buying any dips back toward the 6570-6575 negative gamma cluster. \n\nWatch 6600 as the critical flip level where dealer flow reverses from buying to selling, while any weakness back toward 6570 will trigger intense dealer buying that should provide strong support.",
